https://leetcode.com/problems/clone-graph/description/

QUESTION:
A clone graph is a copy of the graph but the reference changes.

You clone each element and put it in hashmap with the node value and the other being neighbour values(but as nodes)

SOLUTION:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(V+E) V is nodes and E is edges
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(V)
If interviewer asks why not O(V²):

Say:

Because we only traverse each node once and each edge once during BFS traversal.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Input: adjList = [[2,4],[1,3],[2,4],[1,3]]
Output: [[2,4],[1,3],[2,4],[1,3]]
1--------2
|        |
|        |
4--------3
Queue      Map
1          1 [1]
             |
           1 [1,2,4]
2 4        2 [2]
             |
           2 [2 3 1]
           4 [4]
3          3 [3,2,4]
           4 [4,1,3]

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
